olive oil
1 carrot
2 potato
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
2 packet chicken thigh
1 tsp honey
1 apple
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Peri Peri Sauce
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
4 pear
1 packet Classic Oat Mix

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray, then sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning and drizzle with olive oil.
• Toss to coat and season with salt and pepper. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the veggies!

• Meanwhile, combine Nan's special seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt in a large bowl. Add chicken thigh and turn to coat.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray. Drizzle with the honey, then bake until cooked through, 12-14 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple into sticks.
• In a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, apple and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide chicken, herb-roasted veggies and slaw between plates. Top Nan’s baked chicken with peri peri sauce.
• Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!